        <h2>Types of Boilers for Dartford Homes</h2>
        <p>Choosing the right type of boiler for your Dartford property depends on several factors including your property size, number of bathrooms, hot water usage patterns, and available space. At Hixa Heating, we install all types of boilers and can recommend the perfect solution for your specific needs.</p>
        
        <h3>Combi Boilers for Dartford Properties:</h3>
        <p><a href="/combi-boiler-installation/">Combi boilers</a> are the most popular choice for homes in Dartford, particularly for small to medium-sized properties, flats, and apartments. They provide instant hot water on demand without the need for a separate hot water cylinder or cold water tank, making them ideal for properties with limited space. Most 2-4 bedroom homes in Dartford are perfectly suited to a combi boiler.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Flats, terraced houses, semi-detached homes with 1-2 bathrooms, properties with good mains water pressure, and homes where space is at a premium.</p>
        
        <h3>System Boilers for Larger Dartford Homes:</h3>
        <p>System boilers work with a hot water cylinder to store hot water, making them ideal for larger Dartford properties with multiple bathrooms or high simultaneous hot water demand. They're perfect for family homes where several people might need to shower at the same time, or for properties with poor mains water pressure where a combi boiler wouldn't perform well.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Detached houses, larger family homes with 3+ bathrooms, properties with high hot water usage, homes with poor mains pressure, and properties with multiple showers or baths.</p>
        
        <h3>Regular Boilers (Conventional):</h3>
        <p>Regular boilers, also known as conventional or heat-only boilers, are typically found in older Dartford properties. They require both a hot water cylinder and a cold water tank in the loft. While less common in new installations, they're sometimes the best choice for replacing an existing regular boiler in a property with a traditional heating system.</p>
        
        <p>During our free home survey, we'll assess your property and recommend the most suitable boiler type based on your specific requirements, budget, and long-term heating needs.</p>
